                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Anvār-i Suhaylī by Kāshifī, Ḥusayn Vāʻiẓ, d. 1504 or 5
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_326a-item1">
                     <author key="person_90770167" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/90770167/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Kāshifī, Ḥusayn Vāʻiẓ, d. 1504 or 5</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20597" change="#ids-cleanup">Anvār-i Suhaylī</title>
                     <note>There appears to be no record of the registration of the MS before it was entered in Codrington/Reade. It is not among the handwritten additions on the Library copy of Codrington. Defective at beginning and end. The first folio is an irrelevant replacement from the beginning of the Gulzar-i Ibrahim of Zuhuri, mentioning Ibrahim 'Adil Shah. The Anwar-i Suhaili here starts in the account of the discovery of the book in India. Some use of red for headings and punctuation.</note>
                     <incipit>Incipit (f2a): ... padishahan-i buzurg-ra dar qawa'id-i jahandari</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>As for Codrington/Reade No 326.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
